<!-- CycloneDDS config for Go2 EDU + same-host ROS 2 nav stack on this Jetson.

     SINGLE onboard interface eno1, multicast="default" (Unitree standard).
     This matches the host .bashrc + ~/ros2_ws/run_bringup.sh that proved
     Go2 + Ouster driving simultaneously on this box.

     ROOT CAUSE the Go2 was "never discovered" was NOT a DDS-config problem
     (lo / Peers / single-vs-multi interface) — it was UFW dropping the Go2's
     DDS multicast (239.255.0.1) at the host INPUT policy. Fix = `sudo ufw allow
     in on eno1` on the HOST (see docs/jetson-go2-drive-runbook.md). With UFW
     open, same-host discovery and external Go2 multicast both work on a single
     eno1 — no lo, no <Peers>, no AllowMulticast override needed.

     ROS_DOMAIN_ID=0 (Go2 default), set via env. RMW = apt rmw_cyclonedds_cpp
     (CycloneDDS 0.10.x = Go2 SDK2 0.10.2; do NOT rebuild from source on Humble).
     name= the onboard Go2-subnet NIC (192.168.123.x), default eno1; verify with
     `ip a` (NICs/IPs can reshuffle per power-cycle). -->
<CycloneDDS>
  <Domain>
    <General>
      <Interfaces>
        <NetworkInterface name="eno1" priority="default" multicast="default" />
      </Interfaces>
    </General>
  </Domain>
</CycloneDDS>
